What you need to know:

In his processing, he started with a manual production process where no chemicals, machines, electricity or fossil fuel was used. He just needed his hands and some basic utensils.In processing the avocado oil, which is the main product, the retired primary school teacher extracts the pulp from the avocado and smashes it to get a paste.In making the avocado fuel flakes, Mr Mutegi follows the same procedure as in the case of cooking oil, but in this case, utilises the rotten avocados.When burning the avocado flakes, another product, bitumen (tar), is formed. The thick black liquid forms at the bottom of the stove.